          "description": "This chatbot helps students explore Behavior-Based Anomaly Detection in cybersecurity. It explains how AI learns normal user behavior, detects unusual activity, and prevents cyber threats before they escalate.\n\n",
          "intendedUse": "Educational Purposes: Designed to help students understand Behavior-Based Anomaly Detection and how it enhances cybersecurity defenses.\nProject Support: Assists students in applying AI-driven security solutions to their Network Security Risk Assessments.\nGuided Exploration: Encourages students to ask structured questions and think critically about how AI detects cyber threats.\n",
          "limitationsAndWarnings": "Not a real cybersecurity tool: This chatbot provides educational insights only and should not be used for real-world security decisions.\nSimplified explanations: Responses are tailored for students and may not include all technical details used in professional cybersecurity.\nFalse Positives & Privacy Concerns: Anomaly detection can sometimes flag legitimate behavior as suspicious, and AI models require proper tuning to balance accuracy and privacy.\n",
